Flames shot out of Thassalin's maw, as the massive Thracian tied a specific woodland patch with a rope and then circled over it to detect movements. Notably, the ominous screaming behind him subsided as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What's that, Tenuk, you've already turned yourself into a Thracian once!"
"If I were flying myself, it would be entirely different from being suddenly lifted up by a massive pink dragon!"
"So bad as that wasn't it, was it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in Nyssis' opinion. He looked less black than usual and his claws had dug so deep into Thassalin's back that the Thracian was bleeding. Thassalin seemed to take no notice of this, however, it had become clear to him that he had scared his new friends and landed on a clearing.
"I'm sorry, but I had something to take care of. I had to attend to that!"
"But did you have to drag us along too?" growled Tenuk, as he climbed off Thassalin's back and slid down onto its tail. "And we've left Retvik behind! Our big, strong fighter, we've abandoned him! How is he supposed to catch up with us?"
"But he'll come up with something, I'm sure," growled Nyssi. "Retvik may not be the fastest, but he's not stupid."
"But will Retvik be able to drive?"
"But of course he can drive."
"But have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a nice little car like Kayel's. Plus, he only started using the car for work because you always drive us. He only has his bicycle."
Hysterical laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly seemed to find something utterly hilarious, but no one knew what was so funny. It took a bit too long for Thassalin to calm down.
"I'm sorry, but I pictured your enormous friend on such a tiny bicycle for children in Temthar, that was hilarious! I wish I had telepathy, what a wonderful idea! One that I can't share!"
Kayel chuckled, thinking he knew what was going through Thassalin's head. "Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?"
Thassalin grunted, took off and vanished. When he returned shortly afterwards, he threw something lifeless in front of Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, gold-white dragon creature. But it was missing its head. "Another dead one. I hear your screams. I smell your blood. Something urges me to protect and hunt. As Yisini commands. They're getting close."
The massive Thracian suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and watched intently to a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and hissed. Whatever it was, it spread out two enormous pairs of wings and charged at Thassalin, not bothering to avoid the three smaller creatures between them. Kayel and Tenuk barely managed to take cover, but Nyssi was dragged along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by snatching Nyssi and hurling him onto his back with his incredibly long and agile tail, before launching himself into the air. The black, double-winged creature pursued them at high speed.
Kayel clicked angrily, as he took his gun from his back and opened a pouch that contained a cartridge belt. He hung the belt across his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thracian and the monster were out of sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?"
"Do you want to pursue them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a massive monster!"
"Yes, and? I'm standing here with a high-powered gun in my hand and could fire at them right away. But, well, how should I put it – I'd have to be able to see them, in order to hit them."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to give himself more space. With a soft, pained growl, Tenuk's body lengthened, his fur turned to scales and his arms to wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, light blue Thracian, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Like a normal Thracian, Tenuk now had a decent scaly shield running along his back. Conveniently, a pair of spines had also grown on his back, which Kayel could hold onto. It took a little too long for Tenuk to get airborne, but once he was in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they weren't alone. A second dark creature shot up beneath them, and Tenuk could only narrowly avoid a collision.
"That's probably the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel furrowed his brow. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk remained silent, too focused on flying towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature's pursuit. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in sight. The fact that it was pursuing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots went through the upper wings of the beast, it let out a pained roar and sank back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it certainly wouldn't be able to keep up.
A good distance ahead of them, Nyssi was desperately clinging on while Thassalin thrashed about and spat flames at the charred monster. The creature was definitely wounded. It seemed furious but not ready to give in. The fireballs seemed to have the opposite effect. As Thassalin stretched, Nyssi seized the opportunity to pull out her own weapon, an old shot gun. It wasn't the most ideal choice, but maybe the buckshot would deter the black beast.
